{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/building-a-suicidal-tweet-classifier-using-nlp-ff6ccd77e971", "time": 1683012651.7483819, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/building-a-suicidal-tweet-classifier-using-nlp-ff6ccd77e971/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Building a suicidal tweet classifier using NLP | by Israel Aminu | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Building a suicidal tweet classifier using NLP", "description": "Over the years, suicide has been one of the major causes of death worldwide, According to Wikipedia, Suicide resulted in 828,000 global deaths in 2015, an increase from 712,000 deaths in 1990. This\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide#:~:text=Suicides%20resulted%20in%20828%2C000%20global,of%20people%20die%20by%20suicide.", "anchor_text": "Wikipedia", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_media_and_suicide", "anchor_text": "behaviour", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://github.com/AminuIsrael/Optimized-Modified-GetOldTweets3-OMGOT", "anchor_text": "Github", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://github.com/AminuIsrael/Predicting-Suicide-Ideation", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 20}], "all_paragraphs": ["Over the years, suicide has been one of the major causes of death worldwide, According to Wikipedia, Suicide resulted in 828,000 global deaths in 2015, an increase from 712,000 deaths in 1990. This makes suicide the 10th leading cause of death worldwide. There is also increasing evidence that the Internet and social media can influence suicide-related behaviour. Using Natural Language Processing, a field in Machine Learning, I built a very simple suicidal ideation classifier which predict whether a text is likely to be suicidal or not.", "I used a Twitter crawler which I found on Github, made some few changes to the code by removing hashtags, links, URL and symbols whenever it crawls data from Twitter, the data were crawled based on query parameters which contain words like:", "Depressed, hopeless, Promise to take care of, I dont belong here, Nobody deserve me, I want to die etc.", "Although some of the text we\u2019re in no way related to suicide at all, I had to manually label the data which were about 8200 rows of tweets. I also sourced for more Twitter Data and I was able to concatenate with the one I previously had which was enough for me to train.", "I then wrote a function to clean the text data to remove any form of HTML markup, keep emoticon characters, remove non-word character and lastly convert to lowercase.", "After that, I applied the preprocess_tweet function to the tweet dataset to clean the data.", "Then I converted the text to tokens by using the .split() method and used word stemming to convert the text to their root form.", "Then I imported the stopwords library to remove stop words in the text.", "Testing the function on a single text.", "For this project, I used the Hashing Vectorizer because it data-independent, which means that it is very low memory scalable to large datasets and it doesn\u2019t store vocabulary dictionary in memory. I then created a tokenizer function for the Hashing Vectorizer", "Then I created the Hashing Vectorizer object.", "For the Model, I used the stochastic gradient descent classifier algorithm.", "For the model, I used 80% for training and 20% for testing.", "Then I transformed the text data to vectors with the Hashing Vectorizer we created earlier:", "Finally, I then fit the data to the algorithm", "Let's test the accuracy on our test data:", "I had an accuracy of 91% which is fair enough, after that, I then updated the model with the prediction", "I added the text \u201cI\u2019ll kill myself am tired of living depressed and alone\u201d to the model.", "And when I used the following text \u201cIt\u2019s such a hot day, I\u2019d like to have ice cream and visit the park\u201d, I got the following prediction:", "The model was able to predict accurately for both cases. And 